.TH PKGMAN-EDIT 8 "PKGMAN-#VERSION# Manual"

.SH NAME
pkgman-edit \- edit the package's file

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pkgman edit
.IR PKG
.RI [ FILE ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Edit the package \fIFILE\fR from the package source directory
using the editor specified in the $EDITOR environment variable.
If \fIFILE\fR is not specified, 'Pkgfile' is used.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B EDITOR
If the package' source directory has a \fIFILE\fR, then \fBpkgman\fR
will try to open it using a \fBEDITOR\fR. If \fBPAGER\fR is unset,
then \fBpkgman(8)\fR will fail.

.SH SEE ALSO
.B pkgman-ls(8), pkgman-cat(8)

